cies or environment are needed since javassist is transitive. The add-opens setup is for JDK17's runtime tests. If the new generator starts from the current version, it should inherit existing configurations. For fixing issues, the workflow might modify existing tests from version 3.2.21 to 3.3.5, and the user is looking for a deterministic setup. I also think we need to advise on action if agent guidance is present, without adding extra dependencies.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing risks and setup issues**\\n\\nI’m considering the risks of JDK 25 with the SecurityManager permanently disabled. Existing tests should guard against potential issues, especially since behavior may change with version 3.3.5. I need to note that javassist dynamic class generation isn’t supported, meaning tests should check for unsupported features. Also, the JDK native image won't support expression compilation with Javassist. It's crucial that local Gradle and Native Image verifications remain authoritative. Lastly, I must ensure the JSON is valid as a single object without Markdown formatting, and keep my summary concise.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"OGNL has no external service or extra test dependency need; its only runtime dependency is transitive Javassist, but upstream 3.3.5 documents JDK 17+ test JVM opens needed for reflective access.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Configure OGNL tests to run with JVM args `--add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED` and `--add-opens=java.base/java.util=ALL-UNNAMED`; upstream 3.3.5 POM applies these in its JDK 17+ profile. Keep tests focused on normal OGNL parsing/get/set/member-access APIs, and guard SecurityManager-specific assertions because JDK 25 permanently disables SecurityManager behavior.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"JDK 25 changes around SecurityManager can make older tests assert obsolete behavior rather than library functionality.\",\n    \"Expression compilation uses Javassist; native-image runtime may not support all dynamic bytecode generation paths, so tests may need to treat those paths as JVM-only or explicitly handle native-image unsupported-feature failures.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c8e9dcc0c2e1d7f016a416429caf48194a7e3bea17834b900\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1230, "output": 765, "cacheRead": 32768, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34763, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782670365946, "responseId": "resp_0c8e9dcc0c2e1d7f016a41641e642881949148fcb95ed2737e"}, "toolResults": []}
